      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Avalon Borough Council has passed two ordinances intended to help maintain the beach resort's family oriented atmosphere by forbidding any business on the boardwalk to have a liquor license.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Avalon Borough Council has passed two ordinances intended to help maintain the beach resort's family oriented atmosphere by forbidding any business on the boardwalk to have a liquor license.</p>
        <p>The Council unanimously approved ordinances Wednesday night restricting any businesses that sell liquor to existing business zones, which do not include the boardwalk. The action followed an unsuccessful attempt to buy and transfer a liquor license from a restaurant in the business area to another on the boardwalk, said Amy Kleuskens, the Borough Clerk.</p>
      </block>
